    affiliation: California State University, Long Beach
repository-code: "https://github.com/Vinayk393/CECS530-TokenGenerationLatency"
abstract: >
  A controlled, bandwidth-focused benchmarking study of LLaMA-family
  token-generation latency on Apple Silicon (Mac M4 16GB vs Mac M2 8GB).
  Measures TTFT, per-token latency, throughput, cold/warm startup, and
  tail-latency distributions. Memory bandwidth is the primary explanatory
  variable; GPU core count, cache hierarchy, RAM, and OS version are
  acknowledged as residual confounders.
keywords:
  - LLaMA
  - token generation latency
  - Apple Silicon
  - unified memory
  - KV-cache
  - quantization
  - MPS
  - memory bandwidth
  - benchmarking
